line_1: And laughter all their work, is life mispent,
line_2: For tell some men that pleasure all their bent,

line_1: Much are the precious hours of youth mispent,
line_2: In climbing Learning's rugged steep ascent;
How farmers cannot pay their rent;

line_1: Your mind unfurnish'd, and your time mispent.
line_2: Oh! mourn your dross no more: with tears lament
